Our farewell party could not happen in a better place: we were warmly welcomed into @cadorecuritiba by @marina_gwcc , @mcfeliz and @vanessableycolle ,with a welcome drink from @bar_boulevard by @trevisanjor and @felizaus the typical Quentão! 
Ca'dore is the first gastronomic villa in Curitiba, with more than 35 food and beverage options and a sustainable structure of recycled containers.

The business was built on the land of one of the first industries of Paraná and combines a combination of historical preservation and modernity. 
Bar Boulevard also has principles of sustainability such as reverse logistics, use of aluminum straws, organic vegetable garden and social impact suppliers as @criar1 . 
It was a delightful and emotional moment as we knew we would feel SAUDADES from now on! 😪❣️🙏🏻
.
.
.

location.name: UNILIVRE - Universidade Livre do Meio Ambiente

caption.text:
The last part of our inner transformation journey with Flow.in methodology was a solo walk in nature experienced at @unilivre (Bosque Zaninelli), in Curitiba, to allow time outdoors and space for silence, reflection and integration. 
Silence is a condition that enables people to really explore where they are in terms of their own inner transformation process, as well as in the journey of make positive impact. 
Being in nature is a powerful experience, allowing the natural reset for life, while reconnecting us with a greater sense of vitality & renewed purpose. The solo walk in nature allowed participants to deepen their reflection and look honestly at questions of the purpose of their work, their role, and their contributions.
.
.
.
#flowie #impactexperiences #flowin #integralleadership #innerjourney #silence #nature #theoryu #solowalk #unilivre

caption.text:
Our last lunch was in a more than special place: @ahortabikecafe ! 
This business is an incredible example of the combination of the sustainability tripod: balancing economic gain with social development and positive environmental impact! 
In Ahorta Bike Café - besides the 100% vegetarian cafeteria / restaurant with delicious food - there is a communal vegetable garden, green roof, construction in recycled containers, bike workshop, as well as activities such as yoga, meditation, dance and other cultural attractions.  A place that is worth to be visited and that is transforming the entire surrounding region!
.
.
.
Ph: @jannavanessa from @criar1

Check out a little bit of the interview about our social immersion trip in Brazil, produced by @instituto.legado TV together with @deproposito1!

Our social immersion trip was a matter of Legado TV, recorded during our visit to the @instituto.legado ! 
Legado TV is an online audiovisual channel that covers institutional actions and transmits  inedited content about the universe of social entrepreneurship and transforming impact. The content is developed by @deproposito1 
In the interview, journalists asked about Flowie's story, about how this impact experience was designed and also wanted to hear from participants about their perception of Brazil and the field of social impact in the country. Flavia Feliz (@felizflavia) Deena Saunders Green (@dlite001 )Pauline Martinez (@pmventures) and Liziane Silva (@Lizi anesilva3) were interviewed. Link in bio! https://youtu.be/6sWMD-jrctA
